#ROOMS
#3001
The Temple of Midgaard~
White-veined marble columns ring the Temple of Midgaard, their bases worn smooth by generations of pilgrims and adventurers seeking blessing before the road. Incense curls through stained light while votive candles burn in disciplined rows around a central altar of sunstone. A broad stair ascends to the mud school for novices, and avenues radiate outward into a rebuilt city planned with deliberate symmetry.~
